to tell you that

14:42.969 --> 14:45.319
you don't need
to cut me off anymore.

14:47.190 --> 14:49.584
Because he's dead.

14:52.674 --> 14:54.415
What?

15:05.556 --> 15:07.080
What?

15:22.834 --> 15:24.924
Hey.

15:25.837 --> 15:28.057
What did he do to you?

15:28.101 --> 15:30.320
Can you talk to me?

16:09.446 --> 16:12.754
CECILIA: It just doesn't make any sense.

16:14.016 --> 16:15.626
He was...
he was in... he was...

16:15.670 --> 16:19.108
in complete control of
everything, you know? Just...

16:20.501 --> 16:21.981
Including me.

16:22.024 --> 16:26.115
He controlled
how I looked and...

16:26.159 --> 16:29.466
what I wore and what I ate.

16:32.948 --> 16:35.690
And...

16:35.733 --> 16:40.042
then it was controlling
when I left the house and...

16:42.610 --> 16:44.568
...what I said.

16:44.612 --> 16:46.744
And eventually...

16:46.788 --> 16:48.703
what I thought.

16:52.620 --> 16:54.970
And if...

16:55.014 --> 16:59.322
if he didn't like what
he assumed I was thinking...

17:01.194 --> 17:04.153
...h-he... he would...

17:04.197 --> 17:06.025
JAMES:
He'd what? He'd...

17:06.938 --> 17:09.550
He would... he would hit you?

17:10.420 --> 17:12.553
Amongst other things.

17:13.902 --> 17:16.035
He wanted to have a baby.

17:16.078 --> 17:19.429
And I knew that if we did that,
that I...

17:19.473 --> 17:23.303
I would never be able
to get away from him, so...

17:23.346 --> 17:27.568
I took birth control
without him knowing it.

17:27.611 --> 17:32.616
But, um, that can only go on
for so long, so...

17:35.576 --> 17:37.795
I called you.

17:38.927 --> 17:41.060
Hey.

17:43.714 --> 17:45.629
You're here with us now.

17:46.978 --> 17:49.024
And you're safe.

17:49.068 --> 17:51.287
He's gone.

18:18.923 --> 18:20.577
I'm not telling you to aim low.

18:20.621 --> 18:23.145
I'm just saying, e-explore
more than one option, okay?

18:23.189 --> 18:24.407
Don't limit
your choices to just

18:24.451 --> 18:26.017
one school
in the whole country.

18:26.061 --> 18:28.150
But that one school is my goal.

18:28.194 --> 18:29.804
Parsons is my goal.

18:29.847 --> 18:33.460
Yeah, I told you
to have goals--plural.

18:35.549 --> 18:39.074
I think it's important
to have goals, James.

18:39.118 --> 18:40.380
Uh, hey.

18:41.729 --> 18:43.905
Look at you,
getting out into the world.

18:43.948 --> 18:46.864
You know, by next year, you'll
make it across the street.

18:51.173 --> 18:52.435
Uh, hey, Cee.

18:52.479 --> 18:54.220
-Hmm?
-Something came for you.

18:57.005 --> 18:58.920
No one knows I'm here.

19:10.714 --> 19:13.413
JAMES:
So, who's it from?

19:28.689 --> 19:31.387
Thank you both for coming in.

19:32.432 --> 19:34.477
As the appointed attorney

19:34.521 --> 19:37.567
representing my late brother's
discretionary trust,

19:37.611 --> 19:40.788
I'm required to enact
his final wishes.

19:40.831 --> 19:43.660
