that I do this in person.

19:43.704 --> 19:46.185
He wanted me to read a...
a prepared statement.

19:52.974 --> 19:55.455
"Cecilia,

19:55.498 --> 19:58.501
"although our relationship
was far from perfect,

19:58.545 --> 20:00.851
"I at least thought
we had built up enough trust

20:00.895 --> 20:02.070
"that you would talk to me

20:02.113 --> 20:03.724
"rather than running away
from what you

20:03.767 --> 20:05.204
-perceived us to have."
-No, no. Sorry.

20:05.247 --> 20:06.857
You're not allowed to do that.

20:06.901 --> 20:09.382
-I'm required to read this.
-She's not required to listen.

20:09.425 --> 20:11.862
E-mail me a copy,
and we will read it.

20:11.906 --> 20:13.299
You bet.

20:13.342 --> 20:14.691
I'm just trying to do my job.

20:14.735 --> 20:16.171
Your job is
to explain the money

20:16.215 --> 20:18.260
-you mentioned on the phone.
-I mentioned Cecilia

20:18.304 --> 20:20.262
specifically is named
in Adrian's trust.

20:20.306 --> 20:22.046
-That is why we're
sitting here. -Yes.

20:22.090 --> 20:24.310
For the same reason
so many women in Adrian's life

20:24.353 --> 20:26.486
got close to him: his money.

20:26.529 --> 20:28.531
If there was a chance of
physically being close to him,

20:28.575 --> 20:30.446
we would not be here
for any amount of money.

20:30.490 --> 20:32.318
You are physically
close to him.

20:34.320 --> 20:36.235
He's in that urn over there.

20:38.672 --> 20:44.199
And as per his final wishes,
you're getting $5 million,

20:44.243 --> 20:48.377
estate and income tax free.

20:48.421 --> 20:50.118
Now, the money
will be staggered

20:50.161 --> 20:51.902
in installments of $100,000

20:51.946 --> 20:54.601
each month for the next
four years or so,

20:54.644 --> 20:56.820
contingent, of course,
on the fine print.

20:56.864 --> 20:59.040
You can't commit a crime,
et cetera.

20:59.083 --> 21:02.435
Normally, I would have a
120-day contestability period,

21:02.478 --> 21:04.785
but I'm gonna waive my rights
in that regard.

21:04.828 --> 21:06.221
So...

21:06.265 --> 21:08.267
as soon as I have
your signature

21:08.310 --> 21:10.878
and your banking information,

21:10.921 --> 21:12.923
I can start
releasing the funds.

21:23.369 --> 21:25.327
CECILIA:
Okay, you can come in now.

21:30.680 --> 21:32.291
-Uh-oh.
-Oh, hey.

21:32.334 --> 21:34.031
-Wait, wait. Where you at?

21:34.075 --> 21:35.424
-Okay.
-Okay.

21:35.468 --> 21:37.513
-Can we look now?
-CECILIA: Careful.

21:37.557 --> 21:40.124
Yes, you can look.

21:40.168 --> 21:42.213
-Ta-da!
-Oh.

21:42.257 --> 21:44.259
Wow. Thanks, Cee.

21:44.303 --> 21:46.435
Wow, that's nice.
L-Look at that.

21:46.479 --> 21:48.350
-A ladder?

21:48.394 --> 21:49.482
JAMES:
Excuse you?

21:49.525 --> 21:51.527
I know I didn't hear you
just say that.

21:51.571 --> 21:53.834
-I meant to say thank you.
-What do you say? Uh-huh.

21:53.877 --> 21:56.532
You're welcome. Well, I-I knew
you needed a new one,

21:56.576 --> 21:58.665
and that one just...
that has to go.

21:58.708 --> 22:00.971
That's so nice of you, Cee.
Thank you so much.

22:01.015 --> 22:02.973
That's very sweet of you.
Thank you.

22:03.017 --> 22:05.062
I just...
I wanted to thank you for,

22:05.106 --> 22:06.499
you know, letting me stay here

22:06.542 --> 22:09.328
and for taking
such good care of me, so...

22:09.371 --> 22:13.810
And Sydney can also
use ladders.

22:13.854 --> 22:15.638
Don't think
I'm helping you paint.

22:15.682 --> 22:17.597
I wouldn't even bother
to ask you.

22:17.640 --> 22:19.555
No, not for, like,
painting, obviously,

22:19.599 --> 22:21.165
but just for a lot of things.

22:21.209 --> 22:24.081
You climb them to get things
like-like stuff like that.

22:24.125 --> 22:26.083
That's so strange.
God, I wish you had, like...

22:26.127 --> 22:27.302
Oh, wait, you could totally

22:27.346 --> 22:28.651
-use the ladder.
-A ladder to climb up...

22:28.695 --> 22:30.131
Yeah, the ladder's cool.

22:30.174 --> 22:31.828
-Okay. -This happened to just
pop up there by itself?

22:31.872 --> 22:33.352
-It happened to just
be here, so... -Mm-hmm.

22:33.395 --> 22:35.005
-CECILIA: ...it's convenient.
-Wow.

22:35.049 --> 22:36.137
What is it?

22:36.180 --> 22:37.617
-It has my name on it.
-That's weird.

22:37.660 --> 22:39.096
-And it looks like your
handwriting. -I don't know...

22:39.140 --> 22:41.055
-You sure it's weird?
-I just got a ladder, so...

22:41.098 --> 22:42.839
-If you think it's weird.
-I don't know what...

22:42.883 --> 22:44.145
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.
-Let's see.

22:44.188 --> 22:45.929
-A cool ladder is all.

22:48.062 --> 22:50.717
It's a new bank account,
um, with your name on it,

22:50.760 --> 22:54.111
and I'm gonna put
$10,000 in it every month

22:54.155 --> 22:56.113
for the rest of the year.

22:56.157 --> 22:58.986
I called the account "Parsons."

23:03.947 --> 23:05.906
You're going to
fashion school, kid.

23:05.949 --> 23:08.038
Hey, whoa, Cee, Cee, that's...
that's too much, Cee.

23:08.082 --> 23:10.127
Come on, are you sure
you can do that?

23:10.171 --> 23:11.868
Let me put it this way.

23:11.912 --> 23:14.871
: She can probably
go to grad school, too.

23:14.915 --> 23:16.656
I'm going to Parsons.

23:16.699 --> 23:18.353
JAMES :
